homemade ice cream and homemade soda my year old's day camp is having it's last day in week each child has to bring in something they made at home so we can't run to safeway and buy a few cookies and turn it in so i was thinking about ice cream homemade or soda homemade does anybody have a simple recipe or something that a whole lot of year olds will like divine cherry chocolate ice cream ingredients cups heavy cream cups whole milk cup white sugar ounce jar maraschino cherries with juice egg yolks teaspoons almond extract ounces bittersweet chocolate chopped directions stir together cream milk sugar and the juice from the jar of cherries in a large saucepan over medium heat bring to a simmer then remove from heat place the egg yolks into a large bowl then whisk in hot cream about tablespoons at a time until you have added cups whisk the hot yolks into the saucepan of hot cream then cook on low stirring constantly until the mixture reaches degrees f degrees c it will have thickened enough to coat the back of a metal spoon pour the mixture into a container cover and refrigerate until cold about hours chop the reserved maraschino cherries then stir into the cold custard along with almond extract and chopped chocolate pour into ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturer's directions homemade root beer ingredients cups white sugar gallons cold water ounce bottle root beer extract pounds dry ice directions in a large cooler mix together the sugar and water stirring to dissolve sugar completely stir in the root beer extract carefully place the dry ice into the cooler and cover loosely with the lid do not secure the lid as pressure may build up let the mixture brew for about an hour before serving leftover root beer can be stored in one gallon milk jugs homemade chocolate sandwich cookies ingredients ounce packages devil's food cake mix eggs cup shortening directions preheat oven to degrees f degrees c blend the above ingredients together with a pastry blender until mixed roll in balls about the size of a quarter and place on ungreased baking sheets make an even number of balls bake for minutes let cookies stand on cookie sheet for minutes before removing them to cooling rack after cookies have cooled put cream cheese frosting see recipe or use one can of pre made frosting between two cookies putting bottom sides together note adding chopped pecans to the cookies without making them into sandwiches is also very good spice cake mix can be used in place of devil's food Rum Milk Cheese Milkshake Pancake Barbecue Soft drink Beer Wine Halva Cider Wine making Vinegar Haggis Food Cold Stone Creamery Cuisine of Brazil Hamburger Sugar Yoghurt Carbon dioxide Cuisine of Singapore Heath bar Bagel Food preservation Martini cocktail Polish cuisine Peruvian cuisine Sugar beet Recipe Apple pie Pizza Cajun cuisine Cooking weights and measures McDonald's Sangr__a Soup Souffl__ Muesli Plastic Refrigerator Idli Kosher foods Oreo Alcoholic beverage Cuisine of Argentina Horehound Flour Peanut butter Confectionery Champagne (beverage) Gatorade Cantonese cuisine Drink Ketchup French fries Cooking Sushi Cocoa Egg (food) Soy protein Paint Hot chocolate French cuisine Pop-Tarts Soy milk Bacon Casting Baklava Dairy product 